t: To the chief Musician upon Gittith, A Psalm of David.
O*p Lord*s our Lord, how excellent is thy name in all the earth! who hast set thy glory above the heavens.
Out*p of the mouth of babes and sucklings hast thou ordained strength because of thine enemies, that thou mightest still the enemy and the avenger.
When*p I consider thy heavens, the work of thy fingers, the moon and the stars, which thou hast ordained;
What*p is man, that thou art mindful of him? and the son of man, that thou visitest him?
For*p thou hast made him a little lower than the angels, and hast crowned him with glory and honour.
Thou*p madest him to have dominion over the works of thy hands; thou hast put all things under his feet:
All*p sheep and oxen, yea, and the beasts of the field;
The*p fowl of the air, and the fish of the sea, and whatsoever passeth through the paths of the seas.
O*p Lord*s our Lord, how excellent is thy name in all the earth!
